data.text: @sumsion I have a 5D. I love taking portraits and HDR landscapes. I have the 24-105 f/4L, and a 50mm f/1.8. I am more focused on portraits though. That's why I follow you I like to be challenged!
This shot is out of this world! The colours are super!

@deshawn_nwahsed :) you may want to rent a couple of lenses locally. Try them out for a few days before deciding what to buy. There is a huge difference between the 1.8 and the 1.2 for portraits. You could also look at something bigger than a 50mm for portraits.
@sumsion alright! Thats a great idea! I will! I saw one of your pictures where the subject really popped and I am assuming it is from low aperture! Thanks for your help and sharing your knowledge! 
